---
const meta = [
    {
        label: "Currently",
        value: "Architecting an AI-native EMR - clinical workflows, agentic interfaces, the whole stack.",
    },
    {
        label: "Outside of work",
        value: "Gym, bowling, cooking, eating my way through Bengaluru, planning the next trip, or down a YouTube rabbit hole.",
    },
    {
        label: "Based in",
        value: "Bengaluru, India",
    },
];
---

<section
    id="about"
    aria-labelledby="about-heading"
    class="min-h-dvh px-5 sm:px-6 md:px-10 pt-20 sm:pt-24 md:pt-32 pb-16 md:pb-24 flex items-center"
>
    <div class="w-full max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        {/* Hero block */}
        <header class="mb-12 sm:mb-16 md:mb-24 lg:mb-28">
            <p
                class="font-mono text-xs sm:text-[13px] uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-accent mb-4 sm:mb-6"
            >
                Neel Raval
            </p>
            <h1
                id="about-heading"
                class="font-display text-display text-foreground m-0 max-w-[16ch]"
            >
                I build products people didn&rsquo;t know they needed.
            </h1>
        </header>

        {/* Body - photo + bio */}
        <div
            class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 sm:gap-12 md:gap-16 items-start"
        >
            <figure
                class="md:col-span-5 m-0 aspect-5/6 sm:aspect-4/5 overflow-hidden rounded-sm bg-subtle"
            >
                <img
                    src="/neel.webp"
                    alt="Portrait of Neel Raval"
                    width="480"
                    height="600"
                    loading="eager"
                    decoding="async"
                    class="w-full h-full object-cover object-[center_22%] block"
                />
            </figure>

            <div class="md:col-span-7 flex flex-col gap-8 sm:gap-10">
                <p
                    class="font-sans text-base sm:text-[17px] leading-[1.65] text-foreground/90 max-w-[60ch] m-0"
                >
                    I&rsquo;ve been building software since I was in 8th grade -
                    started with Python, mostly self-taught, picked up a B.Tech
                    along the way. These days I&rsquo;m architecting an
                    AI-native EMR from the ground up, and a separate platform
                    that automates the painful manual work of public-sector
                    tendering. The through-line across both - and across most of
                    what I build outside work - is UX. I believe the difference
                    between software that gets adopted and software that gets
                    abandoned is almost always in the interface, in the
                    accessibility, in the small details that make a system feel
                    trustworthy and worth a person&rsquo;s time. I work at the
                    intersection of product, engineering, and design, where
                    craft compounds.
                </p>

                <dl class="flex flex-col gap-5 m-0">
                    {
                        meta.map(({ label, value }) => (
                            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[9rem_1fr] md:grid-cols-[10rem_1fr] gap-2 sm:gap-6">
                                <dt class="font-mono text-[11px] sm:text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.12em] text-muted pt-0 sm:pt-1">
                                    {label}
                                </dt>
                                <dd class="font-sans text-sm sm:text-[15px] leading-[1.55] text-foreground/90 m-0">
                                    {value}
                                </dd>
                            </div>
                        ))
                    }
                </dl>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
